      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(queue): persist followup queues across gateway restarts",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen the gateway process restarts, followup messages queued during an active turn\nare lost. Restored runs must keep reply routing, provenance, and inbound turn\ncontext (room events, quoted replies, bare resets, audio policy).\n\n## Solution\n\nPersist followup queues in shared SQLite (`followup_queue_entries` on\n`openclaw.sqlite`), with doctor migration for legacy `live-chat-followup-queues.json`.\n\n### Persisted per queued item\n\n- Routing: `originatingChannel`, `originatingTo`, `originatingReplyToId`, `originatingChatType`, …\n- Run selectors: `inputProvenance`, `authProfileId`, …\n- Inbound turn context: `currentInboundEventKind`, `currentInboundAudio`, `currentInboundContext`\n- Transcript vs model prompt: `prompt`, `transcriptPrompt`\n\nRuntime-only (not persisted): `abortSignal`, `deliveryCorrelations`, `queuedLifecycle`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Head: `8066e406c`\n- Environment: Linux, Node 24, real `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, real `openclaw.sqlite` I/O\n- Command:\n  ```bash\n  pnpm exec vitest run \\\n    src/auto-reply/reply/queue/persist.test.ts \\\n    src/auto-reply/reply/queue.followup-restart-roundtrip.test.ts \\\n    src/infra/state-migrations.test.ts \\\n    src/infra/followup-queue-sqlite.test.ts\n  ```\n- Result: all tests pass (22 in persist/roundtrip alone on latest run)\n- Covered:\n  - Telegram followup → SQLite → restart → exactly-once redelivery, no replay\n  - Doctor JSON sidecar → SQLite import + restore\n  - Fresh install `followup_queue_entries` table\n  - `room_event`, quoted-reply+audio, bare session-reset context round-trips\n- Not tested: live native Telegram desktop (requires maintainer/write on upstream repo to run Mantis)\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
